FeedPackage.Description: This nuget package is the runtime/redistribuable part of the Visual Studio AdaptiveLINQ extension. AdaptiveLINQ provide the .QueryByCube(), IQueryable extension method. This will help you to build an analysis engine (without needed of any expensive OLAP technology). Define your cubes using the AdaptiveLINQ for Visual Studio extension. Combining with WCF Data Services, your analysis engine will be queryable using OData protocol.

FeedPackage.Description:
This package allows you to easily create responsive xaml code using directly extra properties like X:XS.Column="1", X:XS.Row="3",X:XS.Margin="5,2,8,10", ... This package exists for UWP Win10, Universal App 8.1 and WPF!
Xaml sample:
<Grid> <Grid.ColumnDefinitions> <ColumnDefinition/> <ColumnDefinition/> </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
<X:XS.RowDefinitions> <RowDefinition Height="Auto" /> <RowDefinition Height="Auto" /> </X:XS.RowDefinitions> <X:XS.ColumnDefinitions> <ColumnDefinition/> </X:XS.ColumnDefinitions>
<TextBlock Margin="10" Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="0" X:XS.Margin="2" Text="FirstName"/> <TextBox Margin="10" Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="1" X:XS.Margin="2" X:XS.Row="1" X:XS.Column="0"/> </Grid>
See documentation for more information.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Unique package for all
FeedPackage.Tags: Responsive Adaptive Xaml WPF UWP Windows Store

FeedPackage.Description: This SDK is intended to be integrated by Windows & Windows Phone 8.1 WinRT app/game developers to monetize and/or cross-promote their apps. It supports C#/VB/Unity apps. It provides centered interstitial ads (the most profitable ad format for games and apps), offer wall (Windows Phone only) and 320x50, 728x90, 160x600, 250x250, 173x173, 300x250 banner ad formats. 1:1 cross-promotion services are free, optional and only supported for interstitial & wall ads. Monetization is supported for all ad formats. You will need to create a free account on http://www.addealsnetwork.com to add your app, get your AdDeals AppID/AppKey credentials and access statistics. The SDK can be quickly integrated with couple lines of codes. For Unity games, the SDK can be easily integrated via Visual Studio in C#!

FeedPackage.Description: Are you sick of Add Reference dialog box inside Visual Studio? I am. So here it is. From now on, add your references from PMC (Package Manager Console). For instance, in order to add System.Web as reference to the project named MyApp1, type this; Add-Reference System.Web MyApp1 in order to remove System.Web from the project named MyApp1, type this; Remove-Reference System.Web MyApp1. (Big thanks to @davidfowl for making the code and functions better)

FeedPackage.Description: An Html Helper for MVC 3 that renders the various AddThis buttons and images.
FeedPackage.Title: AddThisHelper

FeedPackage.Description: An Html Helper for MVC 3 that renders the various AddThis buttons and images. Requires an AddThis account for the purpose of AddThis analytic data. Once you have created a new account on AddThis, create an new key in appSettings to store your pubid string. The helper is then called in your view like the following: @RiderDesignMvc.Helpers.AddThisHelper.AddThis32x32. This will will show the AddThis icons that are 32x32.
FeedPackage.Summary: This packaged will install a Html Helper that will render the various button. AddThis. The helper requires an AddThis account for the purpose of AddThis analytic data.
FeedPackage.Title: AddThisHelper

FeedPackage.Description:
An HtmlHelper that easily allows you to enable AddThis functionality with analytic tracking on your MVC 3 site. The helper renders one of 9 AddThis Styles. You can see those 9 types at AddThis.com/Get/Sharing. Before using the helper you will need an AddThis account. This account is for the purposes of analytical data. Go to the AddThis site and register. In your web.config file, create a new entry in appSettings call pubid: <add key="pubid" value="your profile id goes here" /> Once you have installed the package via NuGet, the helper can used in the page of your choice via: @RiderDesignMvc.Helpers.AddThisHelper.AddThis32x32
In this example, the code will render the buttons as 32x32 icons. There are 9 methods that can be called with this helper.
Just call the appropriate method to render the AddThis style of your choice
FeedPackage.Summary: This packaged will install a Html Helper that will render the various button. AddThis. The helper requires an AddThis account for the purpose of AddThis analytic data.
FeedPackage.Title: AddThisHelper
